cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper proposes a deep learning method for estimating per-pixel depth and its uncertainty from a monocular video stream, which is a problem related to computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The method involves Bayesian filtering, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses 3D scene reconstruction, which is a topic related to computer graphics (cs.GR).
